support_summary: No direct interaction is reported. RNF126 is an E3 ligase that ubiquitinates frataxin. While ATXN3 is a deubiquitinase, there is no evidence of it acting on frataxin or interacting with RNF126. The connection is functional through their roles in the ubiquitin-proteasome system. [34, 36]
summary: ATXN3 and RNF126 interact, though the functional significance remains to be fully elucidated.
